27/11/2002
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria has given verbal approval to the United States regarding possible participation in potential military strikes against Iraq, says Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov. 
He spoke Tuesday (26 November), following a luncheon for the ambassadors of NATO states. 
Government spokesman Dimitar Tsonev, however, says Bulgaria has not sent an official reply to Washington. 
(news.bg, Sega - 27/11/02; Mediapool. 
Nova TV - 26/11/02)
